  "title": "Conveyancing Lawyer",
  "description": "<p>We are a boutique conveyancing law firm that is seeking to hire talented lawyers to join our dynamic legal team. We're seeking individuals who are passionate about law and have a strong desire to work in a challenging and dynamic environment.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conducting legal research and drafting legal documents</li>\n  <li>Meeting with clients and discussing legal matters with them</li>\n  <li>Reviewing land registry documents</li>\n  <li>Drafting and reviewing contracts, agreements, and leases related to property transactions</li>\n  <li>Handle and advising clients full range conveyancing matters such as purchase &amp; sales, development projects, mortgages, transfers, leases, powers of attorney, stamp duties and etc. for HDB residential properties, HDB shophouses, private residential properties and commercial/industrial/JTC properties</li>\n  <li>Assisting senior lawyers with complex cases</li>\n  <li>Developing legal strategies for clients</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's degree in Law</li>\n  <li>Valid license to practice law</li>\n  <li>Excellent oral and written communication skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under pressure</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail</li>\n  <li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills</li>\n  <li>Meticulous, well-organized and can work well under time constraints</li>\n  <li>Qualified solicitors with no experience in Conveyancing work are also invited to apply</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive Salary</li>\n  <li>Health Insurance</li>\n  <li>Professional Growth Opportunities</li>\n  <li>Opportunities for further education and training</li>\n  <li>Work life balance working environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>At our law firm, we believe in providing our team members with a supportive and inclusive work environment where they have the tools and resources they need to succeed. We foster a culture of teamwork, collaboration, and excellence, and we're committed to helping our employees grow both personally and professionally.</p>\n<p>If you're a skilled conveyancing lawyer who is looking for a challenging and fulfilling career in the legal profession, we'd love to hear from you. Please email your resume stating current and expected remuneration, reference or testimonial (if any), and your preferred start date to our Managing Director at lionel.yun@tzedeklaw.com.sg&amp; our Business Development Manager at jiaern@tzedeklaw.com.sg.</p>",
